The article discusses a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Donald J. Trump, which delegates certain functions and authorities to various government officials in relation to the Countering America's Adversaries Through Sanctions Act of 2017, the Ukraine Freedom Support Act of 2014, and the Support for the Sovereignty, Integrity, Democracy, and Economic Stability of Ukraine Act of 2014. The memorandum delegates responsibilities to the Secretary of State, the Secretary of the Treasury, and the Director of National Intelligence, among others, regarding the selection and implementation of sanctions, certifications, and other actions outlined in the mentioned acts. The memorandum also states that these delegations will apply to similar provisions in future public laws.